import wordsegment as ws

from wordsegment import load, segment

load()
  
def flat(l):
    for k in l:
        if not isinstance(k, (list, tuple)):
            yield k
        else:
            yield from flat(k)

Splitting¶

In [5]:
# split every characters
data["simplesplit"] = ""
# split special characters
data["specialcharsplit"] = ""
# split words but don't remain the captial characters
data["extrawordsplit"] = ""



for index, row in data.iterrows():
    # simple split for each row
    row['simplesplit'] = list(row['original'])
    row['specialcharsplit'] = re.findall(r'[0-9]+|[a-zA-Z]+|[^a-zA-Z0-9]+',row['original'])
    
    passwdstring=[]
    for i in row['specialcharsplit']:
        templist = segment(i)
        if(templist):
            passwdstring.append(templist)
        else:
            passwdstring.append(i)
    row['extrawordsplit'] = list(flat(passwdstring))
In [6]:
def insertChar(mystring, position, chartoinsert ):
    longi = len(mystring)
    mystring   =  mystring[:position] + chartoinsert + mystring[position:] 
    return mystring

    origin = row['original']

            origin = insertChar(origin,i," ")
    row["fixcapital"] = origin

Define Jaccard function to calculate distance

In [193]:
import itertools 

def jaccard(a, b):
    a = set(list(a))
    b = set(list(b))
    c = a.intersection(b)
    return float(len(c)) / (len(a) + len(b) - len(c))

import numpy as np
l = len(data['plaintext'])
# test for head 100 data
matrix = np.zeros((l, l))
for index, row in data.iterrows():
    # because it is a symmetric matrix
    for i, r in data[index:-1].iterrows():
        matrix[index, i] = jaccard(data.iloc[index]['plaintext'],
                                   data.iloc[i]['plaintext'])
matrix += matrix.T - np.diag(matrix.diagonal())

Try LDA with words only¶

In [66]:
def LDA_words(docs_raw,n_topics):
    tf_vectorizer = CountVectorizer(strip_accents = 'unicode',
                                    stop_words = 'english',
                                    lowercase = True,
                                    # token choose the words with more than 4 length and get rid of the speical words
                                    token_pattern = r'\b[a-zA-Z]{3,}\b',
                                    max_df = 0.5, 
                                    min_df = 10)
    dtm_tf = tf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(**tf_vectorizer.get_params())
    dtm_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    # for TF DTM
    lda_tf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tf.fit(dtm_tf)
    # for TFIDF DTM
    lda_tfidf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tfidf.fit(dtm_tfidf)
    return(lda_tf, dtm_tf, tf_vectorizer)

def LDA_words_numbers(docs_raw,n_topics):
    tf_vectorizer = CountVectorizer(strip_accents = 'unicode',
                                    stop_words = 'english',
                                    lowercase = True,
                                    # token choose the words with more than 4 length and get rid of the speical words
                                    token_pattern = r'\b[a-zA-Z0-9]{3,}\b',
                                    max_df = 0.5, 
                                    min_df = 10)
    dtm_tf = tf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(**tf_vectorizer.get_params())
    dtm_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    # for TF DTM
    lda_tf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tf.fit(dtm_tf)
    # for TFIDF DTM
    lda_tfidf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tfidf.fit(dtm_tfidf)
    return(lda_tf, dtm_tf, tf_vectorizer)

Estimation $$Qij = \frac{num:\_from\_i\_to\_j}{num:\_from\_i}$$ If the num of events from i is zero, then the whole row is 0

It is just a 1-step markov chain. so from i to j, we just need to find the largest probability.

In [116]:
def findthemax(matrix, string, alphabet):
    position = alphabet.index(string[-1])
    for i in range(len(matrix[position])):
        if matrix[position, i] == (max(matrix[position])):
            print(alphabet[i])
            return (i)


def findthemin(matrix, string, alphabet):
    position = alphabet.index(string[-1])
    for i in range(len(matrix[position])):
        if matrix[position, i] == (min(matrix[position])):
            print(alphabet[i])
            return (i)


def generatemax(matrix, string, alphabet):
    print(string, end='')
    while (string[-1] != '停'):
        position = alphabet.index(string[-1])
        for i in range(len(matrix[position])):
            if matrix[position, i] == (max(matrix[position])):
                print(alphabet[i], end='')
                string = string + alphabet[i]


def generatebyQ(matrix, string, alphabet):
    from bisect import bisect
    from random import random
    print(string, end='')
    j = 0
    while (string[-1] != '停'):
        if j > 5:
            break
        position = alphabet.index(string[-1])
        # choose string by the transition matrix
        P = matrix[position]
        cdf = [P[0]]
        for i in range(1, len(P)):
            cdf.append(cdf[-1] + P[i])

        random_ind = bisect(cdf, random())
        if alphabet[random_ind] != '停':
            print(alphabet[random_ind], end='')
        string = string + alphabet[random_ind]
        j += 1

import random


def generatebyQQ(matrix, alphabet):
    from bisect import bisect
    from random import random

    string = alphabet[np.random.randint(len(alphabet))]
    print(string, end='')
    j = 0
    while (string != '停'):
        if j >= 3:
            break
        position = alphabet.index(string)
        # choose string by the transition matrix
        P = matrix[position]
        cdf = [P[0]]
        for i in range(1, len(P)):
            cdf.append(cdf[-1] + P[i])

        random_ind = bisect(cdf, random())
        if alphabet[random_ind] != '停':
            print(alphabet[random_ind], end='')
        string = alphabet[random_ind]
        j = j + 1

In [128]:
import random


class MarkovChain:

    def __init__(self):
        self.memory = {}

    def _learn_key(self, key, value):
        if key not in self.memory:
            self.memory[key] = []

        self.memory[key].append(value)

    def learn(self, text):
        tokens = text.split(" ")
        bigrams = [(tokens[i], tokens[i + 1]) for i in range(0, len(tokens) - 1)]
        for bigram in bigrams:
            self._learn_key(bigram[0], bigram[1])

    def _next(self, current_state):
        next_possible = self.memory.get(current_state)

        if not next_possible:
            next_possible = self.memory.keys()

        return random.sample(next_possible, 1)[0]

    def babble(self, amount, state=''):
        if not amount:
            return state

        next_word = self._next(state)
        return state + ' ' + self.babble(amount - 1, next_word)

def pswd_analyse(results):
    mylist = []
    for i in range(len(results['sequence'])):
        for key, val in results['sequence'][i].items():
            if key == 'pattern':
                if val == 'dictionary':
                    #if results['sequence'][i]['dictionary_name'] != 'passwords':
                    mylist.append(results['sequence'][i]['dictionary_name'])
                elif val == 'sequence':
                    mylist.append(results['sequence'][i]['sequence_name'])
                elif val == 'regex':
                    mylist.append(results['sequence'][i]['regex_name'])
                elif val == 'date':
                    mylist.append(val)
                elif val == 'bruteforce':
                    mylist.append(val)
                elif val == 'repeat':
                    mylist.append(val)
                elif val == 'spatial':
                    mylist.append(val)
                else:
                    mylist.append(val)
                    print(val)
                    print(results)
    return(mylist)

def LDA_pwstrenth(docs_raw,n_topics):
    tf_vectorizer = CountVectorizer(strip_accents = 'unicode',
                                    stop_words = ['english','aren','doesn','this','very','don','like','much','than','help','thems'],
                                    lowercase = True,
                                    # token choose the words with more than 4 length and get rid of the speical words
                                    token_pattern = r'\b[a-zA-Z0-9]{3,}\b',
                                    max_df = 0.5, 
                                    min_df = 10)
    dtm_tf = tf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    tfidf_vectorizer = TfidfVectorizer(**tf_vectorizer.get_params())
    dtm_tfidf = tfidf_vectorizer.fit_transform(docs_raw)
    # for TF DTM
    lda_tf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tf.fit(dtm_tf)
    # for TFIDF DTM
    lda_tfidf = LatentDirichletAllocation(n_components=n_topics, random_state=0)
    %time lda_tfidf.fit(dtm_tfidf)
    return(lda_tf, dtm_tf, tf_vectorizer)
